<paragraph id="8BFD36D5861E6B38FECF8786FD40F3EE" blockId="12.[230,1220,2920,3189]" pageId="12" pageNumber="75">
Type locality. 
<quantity id="4CBA9B30861E6B38FDF68786FD01F382" box="[558,667,3058,3097]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="12" pageNumber="75" unit="m" value="150.0">150 m</quantity>
west of 'Marohn' homestead, on the Scone-Gundy roadside, 
<quantity id="4CBA9B30861E6B38FC988054FC30F3DD" box="[832,938,3104,3142]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="12" pageNumber="75" unit="km" value="4.0">4 km</quantity>
south-west of Gundy, NSW (Locality 28).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFD36D5861E6B38FAE28DEFF8E1FE6B" blockId="12.[1287,2269,411,1188]" pageId="12" pageNumber="75">Stratigraphic position. In bioclastic limestone, upper part of the Dangarfield Formation.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFD36D5861E6B38FAE28D83F8BAFDE0" blockId="12.[1287,2269,411,1188]" pageId="12" pageNumber="75">Additional material. 25 from Swains Gully (Locality 25), 6 from south-east of 'Rangari' (Locality 18) and 6 from Glenbawn (Locality 31).</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFD36D5861E6B38FAE28EF6F72DFD32" blockId="12.[1287,2269,411,1188]" box="[1338,2231,642,681]" pageId="12" pageNumber="75">Geographic distribution. 'Rangari' to Glenbawn.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFD36D5861E6B38FAE28EC4F7CFFD4C" blockId="12.[1287,2269,411,1188]" box="[1338,2133,688,727]" pageId="12" pageNumber="75">Geological age. Middle to late Tournaisian.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C358655E861E6B38FAE18EABF8A1FCF9" pageId="12" pageNumber="75" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BFD36D5861E6B38FAE18EABF8A1FCF9" blockId="12.[1287,2269,411,1188]" pageId="12" pageNumber="75">
Etymology. Derived from the Latin 
<emphasis id="B936EAC7861E6B38F8118EABF7ADFC9D" box="[1993,2103,735,774]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="75">radian</emphasis>
meaning radial, and nodosusmeaning nodose; referring to the radial nodes below the sutures.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C358655E861E6B38FAE18F1DF709FB3F" pageId="12" pageNumber="75" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BFD36D5861E6B38FAE18F1DF709FB3F" blockId="12.[1287,2269,411,1188]" pageId="12" pageNumber="75">
Remarks. This form differs from the only described Australian species, 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D56861E6B38F9828FE3FAF0FC76" authority="Campbell &amp; Engel" authorityName="Campbell &amp; Engel" class="Gastropoda" family="Gosseletinidae" genus="Angyomphalus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pleurotomariida" pageId="12" pageNumber="75" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="depressa">
<emphasis id="B936EAC7861E6B38F9828FE3F862FC25" box="[1626,2040,919,958]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="75">Angyomphalus depressa</emphasis>
Campbell &amp; Engel
</taxonomicName>
in that the latter has a low spired shell with more acute periphery and more closely spaced and longer nodes just below the suture. It resembles the Belgian type species 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D56861E6B38FA4F883BF739FBED" authority="(de Koninck, 1881)" baseAuthorityName="de Koninck" baseAuthorityYear="1881" box="[1431,2211,1103,1142]" class="Gastropoda" family="Gosseletinidae" genus="Angyomphalus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pleurotomariida" pageId="12" pageNumber="75" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="radians">
<emphasis id="B936EAC7861E6B38FA4F883BF8B1FBED" box="[1431,1835,1103,1142]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="75">Angyomphalus radians</emphasis>
(de 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD34B24861E6B38F849883BF70DFBED" author="Koninck, L. G. de" box="[1937,2199,1103,1142]" pageId="12" pageNumber="75" pagination="1 - 157" refId="ref26476" refString="Koninck, L. G. de, 1881. Faune du calcaire Carbonifere de la Belgique. Gasteropodes. Musee Royal d'Histoire Naturelle de Belgique Annales 6: 1 - 157." type="journal article" year="1881">Koninck, 1881</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
ill shell character but differs in being much smaller.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
